1
00:00:32,739 --> 00:00:34,104
Cambodia.

2
00:00:35,235 --> 00:00:37,965
To many Westerners,
it seemed a paradise.

3
00:00:38,050 --> 00:00:41,213
Another world, a secret world.

4
00:00:41,378 --> 00:00:45,314
But the war in neighboring
Vietnam burst its borders...

5
00:00:45,346 --> 00:00:48,873
...and the fighting soon spread
to neutral Cambodia.

6
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:52,830
In 1973, I went to cover
this sideshow struggle...

7
00:00:52,896 --> 00:00:55,990
...as foreign correspondent
of The New York Times.

8
00:00:56,225 --> 00:00:58,989
It was there, amidst the fighting...

9
00:00:59,072 --> 00:01:02,405
...between government troops
and the Khmer Rouge guerrillas...

10
00:01:02,463 --> 00:01:06,058
...that I met my guide
and interpreter, Dith Pran...

11
00:01:06,111 --> 00:01:09,103
...a man who was to change my life...

12
00:01:09,182 --> 00:01:12,151
...in a country that I grew to love
and pity.

13
00:01:20,861 --> 00:01:23,659
So here we go
with Voice of America...

14
00:01:23,741 --> 00:01:25,732
...news for Southeast Asia.

15
00:01:25,852 --> 00:01:29,982
It's 6:45 and a partly cloudy
morning here.

16
00:01:30,012 --> 00:01:32,276
Clouds too in Washington.

17
00:01:32,379 --> 00:01:36,145
President Nixon announced he'll
address the nation on Watergate...

18
00:01:36,187 --> 00:01:38,052
...within the next few days.

19
00:01:38,170 --> 00:01:40,798
The speech will be Nixon's
first since May.

20
00:01:42,458 --> 00:01:46,485
The scandal has caused resignations
and paralyzed the White House staff.

21
00:01:46,521 --> 00:01:50,116
It has also led to intense
confrontation and perhaps...

22
00:01:50,169 --> 00:01:53,036
...a constitutional crisis
with Senate investigators...

23
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:55,741
...and a special
Watergate prosecutor.

24
00:01:55,832 --> 00:01:59,199
The speech was announced
after the Gallup Poll disclosed...

25
00:01:59,256 --> 00:02:03,124
...that Mr. Nixon's popularity
had fallen to the lowest point...

26
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:05,957
...for an American President
in 20 years.

27
00:02:17,173 --> 00:02:19,937
A Supreme Court judge,
William O. Douglas...

28
00:02:20,021 --> 00:02:22,990
...has ruled against an appeal
by the Administration...

29
00:02:23,061 --> 00:02:24,722
...for a stay of the injunction...

30
00:02:24,852 --> 00:02:28,344
...on further U.S. Bombing
missions in Cambodia.

31
00:02:28,404 --> 00:02:31,396
Congress has already ruled
these bombings illegal...

32
00:02:31,475 --> 00:02:35,741
...and they should cease in one
week's time on August the 15th.

33
00:02:56,144 --> 00:02:58,135
Let's go, Sarun!
To the hospital!

34
00:03:16,237 --> 00:03:18,364
Information. Information.

35
00:03:18,477 --> 00:03:23,414
Air Cambodia regret delays of arrival
of flight number 125...

36
00:03:23,404 --> 00:03:27,033
...from Bangkok because
of bad weather.

37
00:03:47,433 --> 00:03:49,560
Mister, you want taxi?

38
00:03:49,672 --> 00:03:51,936
Mister, you want taxi?
Good taxi.

39
00:04:18,245 --> 00:04:21,305
Shut the fucking blinds, will you?

40
00:04:25,412 --> 00:04:27,073
What's all this shit?

41
00:04:29,924 --> 00:04:31,323
I'm sorry.

42
00:04:32,035 --> 00:04:35,402
I thought you were the houseboy.
I was developing some film.

43
00:04:35,746 --> 00:04:39,307
If you're gonna yell, I'll come back.
I'm not feeling good.

44
00:04:39,362 --> 00:04:41,796
Don't want to yell.
I want to be in a good mood.

45
00:04:41,890 --> 00:04:44,825
The plane was late, no car.
I had to take a taxi here.

46
00:04:44,897 --> 00:04:47,263
All I want to do is work.
I got you.

47
00:04:56,736 --> 00:04:59,068
What the fuck is that on your head?

48
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:04,867
It's a sanitary napkin.
I had it soaked in ice.

49
00:05:06,302 --> 00:05:08,964
Syd Schanberg.
Is Pran there?

50
00:05:10,653 --> 00:05:12,780
No, I just came from the airport.

51
00:05:13,597 --> 00:05:16,589
Well, if he comes in,
would you tell him I'm here?

52
00:05:16,797 --> 00:05:19,288
I'll be at the Café Central, tell him.

53
00:05:19,644 --> 00:05:20,633
Thanks a lot.

54
00:05:37,723 --> 00:05:38,917
What do you want to eat?

55
00:05:40,890 --> 00:05:41,754
Want some eggs?

56
00:05:41,914 --> 00:05:45,441
I can't. Somebody told me they faint
with fright when you cook them.

57
00:05:45,497 --> 00:05:47,727
- What do you want to eat?
- What are you having?

58
00:05:47,832 --> 00:05:49,390
I'm having a café complet.

59
00:05:49,945 --> 00:05:52,311
I'll have that. And some aspirin.

60
00:05:59,639 --> 00:06:03,200
Anything I eat has got to be
absolutely dead.

61
00:06:03,254 --> 00:06:05,154
That's why I can never eat an oyster.

62
00:06:05,655 --> 00:06:08,590
I read somewhere that they put...

63
00:06:10,710 --> 00:06:14,339
...that lemon juice on them
just to stun them. You know?

64
00:06:14,389 --> 00:06:15,549
What's the difference?

65
00:06:16,917 --> 00:06:21,354
An unconscious oyster's just as
horrible as the fucker wide awake...

66
00:06:34,899 --> 00:06:37,299
- My God! Look at this.
- Did you see that?

67
00:06:37,394 --> 00:06:38,725
What was it? A rocket?

68
00:06:38,866 --> 00:06:41,562
I don't know.
I saw a guy on a motorbike.

69
00:06:49,968 --> 00:06:51,401
I've been looking for you.

70
00:06:51,536 --> 00:06:53,094
I left a message for you.

71
00:06:53,232 --> 00:06:55,257
I didn't get it. I took a cab.

72
00:06:55,375 --> 00:06:58,310
- There is a big accident right now.
- What?

73
00:06:58,383 --> 00:07:01,750
I think U.S. Drop many big bombs
on little city.

74
00:07:02,094 --> 00:07:05,120
- U.S. Bombs? You're sure?
- I think many dead.

75
00:07:05,198 --> 00:07:07,689
- Does anybody else know about it?
- Nothing at all.

76
00:07:08,526 --> 00:07:09,584
We're going.

77
00:07:09,806 --> 00:07:12,297
Not possible right now, Sydney.
Too dangerous.

78
00:07:39,402 --> 00:07:41,199
Where you going, Schanberg?

79
00:07:42,633 --> 00:07:44,066
Neak Luong.

80
00:07:44,201 --> 00:07:45,463
Neak Luong's closed.

81
00:07:45,609 --> 00:07:49,375
Don't give me that, Reeves.
You got nothing to say about this.

82
00:07:49,416 --> 00:07:52,908
I got a right to go wherever I like
in this sad little country.

83
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:57,870
That's the law. You impede me, you're
breaking the Cooper/Church Amendment!

84
00:07:57,863 --> 00:08:00,730
Well, up the Cooper/Church
Amendment's ass!

85
00:08:03,078 --> 00:08:04,238
Let's go!

86
00:08:14,692 --> 00:08:16,785
So how can I help you, Mr. Schanberg?

87
00:08:20,580 --> 00:08:25,483
I'm looking for information on why
my airplane was delayed this morning.

88
00:08:26,563 --> 00:08:28,758
- Your plane was delayed?
- That's right.

89
00:08:28,867 --> 00:08:32,166
I don't know. Maybe it's
bad weather. Your flight's...

90
00:08:32,226 --> 00:08:34,285
You don't know anything about it?

91
00:08:34,914 --> 00:08:35,972
No, I don't.

92
00:08:36,386 --> 00:08:37,375
All right.

93
00:08:39,105 --> 00:08:41,596
Then I'd like you
to listen to something...

94
00:08:41,697 --> 00:08:43,722
...and then I'd like a comment.

95
00:08:44,001 --> 00:08:47,698
This morning, for reasons beyond
anybody's control...

96
00:08:47,744 --> 00:08:51,840
...I spend two hours in Bangkok
staring at a seat belt sign.

97
00:08:51,871 --> 00:08:53,429
Meanwhile, my sources tell me...

98
00:08:53,568 --> 00:08:57,368
...two Army helicopters are landing
here, just across the airfield.

99
00:08:57,759 --> 00:09:01,024
Half the ambulances in Phnom Penh
are waiting there to meet them.

100
00:09:01,278 --> 00:09:05,442
And now there's a rumor that
the U.S. Air Force dropped a bomb...

101
00:09:05,470 --> 00:09:07,370
...or several bombs, on Neak Luong.

102
00:09:07,485 --> 00:09:10,648
That's a rumor, and I'm not gonna
comment on a rumor.

103
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:14,778
I just want to know if that's the
reason why my airplane was delayed!

104
00:09:18,332 --> 00:09:19,299
No comment.

105
00:09:20,188 --> 00:09:21,348
How many killed?

106
00:09:24,252 --> 00:09:25,549
How many wounded?

107
00:09:30,842 --> 00:09:33,572
Thank you for your cooperation,
Major Reeves.

108
00:09:35,642 --> 00:09:39,874
When I scrape this story out, I will
no doubt be quoting you in full!

109
00:10:20,820 --> 00:10:21,946
I'm sorry.

110
00:10:22,451 --> 00:10:24,419
This is just not good enough.

111
00:10:24,531 --> 00:10:26,522
This is a big story...

112
00:10:26,643 --> 00:10:30,875
...a major story, you understand that?
We've got to get down there!

113
00:10:30,898 --> 00:10:32,991
- I know, but...
- I don't want to hear "no"!

114
00:10:33,106 --> 00:10:35,097
I want to get down that river!

115
00:10:35,218 --> 00:10:36,947
We should be down there now!

116
00:10:48,752 --> 00:10:50,083
I'll be here.

117
00:10:52,496 --> 00:10:53,986
Good night, Sydney.

118
00:11:02,670 --> 00:11:04,433
- Messages?
- No, sir.

119
00:11:04,878 --> 00:11:05,867
No, sir.

120
00:11:07,789 --> 00:11:11,020
I'd talk, but it's been
a heavy day and I've got to go.

121
00:11:11,085 --> 00:11:13,553
Let's get together again soon, okay?

122
00:11:13,644 --> 00:11:15,009
- Bob?
- See you.

123
00:11:15,404 --> 00:11:16,371
Bob?

124
00:11:17,388 --> 00:11:19,379
Hello, Sydney. Good night, Sydney.

125
00:11:19,499 --> 00:11:22,696
- Listen, I can't talk with you.
- You can talk to me.

126
00:11:22,764 --> 00:11:25,733
The embassy is jittery.
Get information from a press officer.

127
00:11:25,802 --> 00:11:28,100
Let's not start insulting each other.

128
00:11:30,218 --> 00:11:31,845
Good night, Sydney.

129
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:34,117
All right, good night.

130
00:11:39,305 --> 00:11:41,170
You've heard of pilot error?

131
00:11:41,289 --> 00:11:42,779
Computer malfunction?

132
00:11:43,144 --> 00:11:45,044
They screwed up on the coordinates.

133
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:48,926
A single B-52 dropped
its entire load on Neak Luong.

134
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:53,136
There's a homing beacon
in the middle of the town.

135
00:11:54,567 --> 00:11:56,558
- Casualties?
- You'll be briefed tomorrow.

136
00:11:56,678 --> 00:12:01,377
We estimate 55 military,
something like 35 civilians.

137
00:12:02,566 --> 00:12:03,794
How many?

138
00:12:06,054 --> 00:12:08,852
I hear it's in the hundreds.
Don't quote me on that.

139
00:12:08,933 --> 00:12:12,198
Will there be a dreadful bloodbath

140
00:12:12,261 --> 00:12:15,355
When the Khmer Rouge hit the town?

141
00:12:15,684 --> 00:12:18,380
Will there be a dreadful bloodbath...?

142
00:12:20,868 --> 00:12:23,063
Beer! We haven't had this
for four weeks.

143
00:12:23,363 --> 00:12:25,263
New York Times probably
had it flown in.

144
00:12:25,763 --> 00:12:29,164
- They keep it in their suite.
- We got a cellar. Don't you know?

145
00:12:29,218 --> 00:12:31,686
Americans take themselves so seriously.

146
00:12:31,778 --> 00:12:36,579
Don't be hard on the man. He's just
trying to get to the top of the heap.

147
00:12:36,578 --> 00:12:40,173
We'll just have to pay more to get
our telexes to the top of the heap.

148
00:12:40,224 --> 00:12:42,749
The man has just bought you a beer.
Now drink up.

149
00:12:42,848 --> 00:12:43,906
- Cheers.
- Cheers, Syd.

150
00:12:44,064 --> 00:12:46,055
- Enjoy it.
- Off to see the telex operator?

151
00:12:46,176 --> 00:12:48,576
- New York Times goes to bed early.
- Sure!

152
00:12:50,143 --> 00:12:52,907
Khmer Rouge in the sunset

153
00:12:54,143 --> 00:12:56,577
The Yanks all at sea...

154
00:13:00,158 --> 00:13:02,251
- All right?
- Very possible.

155
00:13:03,294 --> 00:13:04,761
Let's go then!

156
00:13:12,381 --> 00:13:13,871
This is good work.

157
00:13:48,951 --> 00:13:50,509
- How much?
- Hundred fifty.

158
00:13:57,494 --> 00:13:58,483
One hundred!

159
00:14:04,245 --> 00:14:05,712
- All right?
- All right.

160
00:14:13,173 --> 00:14:14,868
Nice going, Pran.

161
00:15:11,148 --> 00:15:13,810
- What is he saying?
- He wants you to look at his family.

162
00:15:13,899 --> 00:15:18,336
To take a photograph and help him
because his child was wounded.

163
00:15:43,592 --> 00:15:45,685
Tell me what she's saying.

164
00:15:47,815 --> 00:15:49,305
She needs help.

165
00:15:53,031 --> 00:15:55,659
Her shop was destroyed last night.

166
00:15:56,710 --> 00:15:58,143
Her husband killed.

167
00:15:58,278 --> 00:15:59,506
How many bombs?

168
00:16:01,318 --> 00:16:02,580
She doesn't know.

169
00:16:03,589 --> 00:16:05,614
Does she know where the hospital is?

170
00:16:07,237 --> 00:16:08,568
"Just over there."

171
00:16:14,564 --> 00:16:16,794
She wants to know,
"Did someone arrest the pilot?"

172
00:16:19,235 --> 00:16:22,033
Mister, you wanna buy?
Mister, you wanna buy?

173
00:16:22,275 --> 00:16:25,506
- One dollar? You wanna buy?
- I'm out of film. I'm sorry.

174
00:16:26,498 --> 00:16:29,467
Ask her how many kids she's got
in her family.

175
00:16:30,561 --> 00:16:31,425
"Five."

176
00:16:31,842 --> 00:16:34,276
Her husband was killed already.

177
00:16:38,305 --> 00:16:39,567
What's this?

178
00:16:39,968 --> 00:16:41,731
What are these guys over here?

179
00:16:46,783 --> 00:16:49,684
In the jeep, prisoners.
Khmer Rouge prisoners.

180
00:17:11,740 --> 00:17:13,731
They kill a lot of villagers.

181
00:17:14,012 --> 00:17:16,572
She says Khmer Rouge soak rags
in gasoline...

182
00:17:16,667 --> 00:17:18,692
...and push them down
villagers' throat...

183
00:17:18,811 --> 00:17:20,802
...then set the rags alight.

184
00:17:20,954 --> 00:17:22,114
Film! No film!

185
00:17:22,267 --> 00:17:23,757
I know there's no film.

186
00:17:23,898 --> 00:17:25,024
No camera!

187
00:17:26,202 --> 00:17:27,260
No camera!

188
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:28,740
It's all right.

189
00:17:31,545 --> 00:17:32,978
Just take it easy.

190
00:17:38,648 --> 00:17:40,206
Tell them we're jour...

191
00:17:49,431 --> 00:17:50,830
Come on! Get in!

192
00:18:33,137 --> 00:18:34,764
I'm worried.

193
00:18:36,080 --> 00:18:38,480
I'm the guy who bring you over here.

194
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:41,350
They accuse me and they arrest me.

195
00:18:41,808 --> 00:18:44,299
How can they arrest you?
You're already arrested.

196
00:18:45,647 --> 00:18:47,638
They phone Phnom Penh about me.

197
00:18:56,526 --> 00:18:58,016
I want some cigarettes.

198
00:19:00,045 --> 00:19:01,512
And I need to take a leak.

199
00:19:04,493 --> 00:19:06,484
Would you tell them I need to piss?

200
00:19:29,577 --> 00:19:31,067
He said, "No piss."

201
00:19:32,777 --> 00:19:33,903
What does that mean?

202
00:19:34,376 --> 00:19:36,241
That's no piss.

203
00:19:40,488 --> 00:19:42,718
I've had enough of this bullshit.

204
00:19:43,271 --> 00:19:45,262
I got a story to get to New York!

205
00:19:50,214 --> 00:19:51,511
Don't leave me!

206
00:20:01,893 --> 00:20:03,155
I won't leave you.

207
00:21:09,116 --> 00:21:11,516
They brought in the whole press corps!

208
00:21:11,612 --> 00:21:14,945
They want to sanitize the story!
Bastards!

209
00:21:24,825 --> 00:21:26,952
I am going to tell you something.

210
00:21:27,097 --> 00:21:28,758
I'm walking out of here.

211
00:21:28,889 --> 00:21:31,221
What are you gonna do?
Blow my head off?

212
00:21:31,384 --> 00:21:34,376
You got a general out there,
this is an American passport...

213
00:21:34,457 --> 00:21:36,391
...and I am walking out of here!

214
00:21:38,967 --> 00:21:42,232
- He wants to get higher officer.
- Then get him! Get him!

215
00:21:50,166 --> 00:21:54,296
I'm sorry we couldn't show you the
minor bomb damage in the city itself.

216
00:21:54,325 --> 00:21:56,122
It's still a restricted area.

217
00:21:56,245 --> 00:21:58,509
Now, if you look across the river...

218
00:21:58,613 --> 00:22:01,548
...you'll see positions held by
Khmer Rouge...

219
00:22:01,621 --> 00:22:03,418
...who moved in over
the past few days.

220
00:22:03,540 --> 00:22:06,771
But the Cambodian Republican Army
is moving in on them.

221
00:22:06,836 --> 00:22:10,328
They'll have the K.R. Out
before you can say "Jack Robinson."

222
00:22:11,059 --> 00:22:12,754
Get in the chopper now!

223
00:22:12,979 --> 00:22:16,437
No, Schanberg! You came on a boat,
you go back on a boat!

224
00:22:16,498 --> 00:22:18,693
That won't stop my story!

225
00:22:21,234 --> 00:22:22,166
What is this?

226
00:22:22,322 --> 00:22:25,348
If you weren't down here,
I wouldn't be down here.

227
00:22:25,426 --> 00:22:28,327
And I don't want to be down here!
What good is it doing?

228
00:22:28,401 --> 00:22:30,232
If anybody ever reads about this...

229
00:22:30,353 --> 00:22:33,049
...you won't be able to look them
in the face!

230
00:23:11,467 --> 00:23:12,661
Good morning.

231
00:23:13,419 --> 00:23:14,408
What time is it?

232
00:23:16,266 --> 00:23:17,790
Six o'clock.

233
00:23:19,114 --> 00:23:20,012
Shit.

234
00:23:20,170 --> 00:23:21,398
Telex for you.

235
00:23:21,962 --> 00:23:23,429
You been to the telex?

236
00:23:25,673 --> 00:23:27,038
We made the front page.

237
00:23:27,177 --> 00:23:28,144
Sure.

238
00:23:30,120 --> 00:23:32,179
We must be doing something right.

239
00:23:39,751 --> 00:23:42,345
My wife is very worried.

240
00:23:42,855 --> 00:23:46,450
She thinks all foreign journalists
are going to leave Cambodia.

241
00:23:47,750 --> 00:23:49,183
Well, Pran...

242
00:23:50,278 --> 00:23:54,681
...l'd feel kind of stupid trying to
cover this war from a desk in Bangkok.

243
00:23:55,877 --> 00:23:58,971
And she said if the war
keeps going like this...

244
00:23:59,045 --> 00:24:01,206
...the future could be very bad.

245
00:24:02,916 --> 00:24:04,213
What do you think?

246
00:24:07,108 --> 00:24:08,439
I don't know.

247
00:24:10,787 --> 00:24:12,152
I don't know either.

248
00:24:14,755 --> 00:24:16,723
- Is Sarun downstairs?
- Sure.

249
00:24:17,826 --> 00:24:19,225
Let's get going.

250
00:24:20,098 --> 00:24:21,065
All right.

251
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:28,337
