01:45:39,343 --> 01:45:41,903
Abe, meet my sister.

752
01:45:41,999 --> 01:45:43,830
I'm very happy to meet you.

753
01:45:43,951 --> 01:45:46,420
That's my dad.
Would you hold this for me?

754
01:45:47,375 --> 01:45:48,342
One second.

755
01:45:48,495 --> 01:45:51,692
I hoped you could recommend
a good school for journalism.

756
01:45:51,759 --> 01:45:54,729
I told my daughter I'd be
seeing you today.

757
01:45:54,799 --> 01:45:57,666
Just one minute, okay?
I'll be right back.

758
01:46:06,318 --> 01:46:10,118
Could I have your autograph?
I'm a great admirer of yours.

759
01:46:12,463 --> 01:46:15,159
Congratulations on your award,
it was well-deserved.

760
01:46:15,247 --> 01:46:18,512
Very impressive.
I was hoping you'd burst into song.

761
01:46:19,791 --> 01:46:22,521
- What are you doing here?
- You know what bothers me?

762
01:46:22,606 --> 01:46:23,436
What?

763
01:46:23,791 --> 01:46:26,487
It bothers me that you let Pran
stay in Cambodia...

764
01:46:26,573 --> 01:46:29,702
...because you wanted to win,
and you knew you needed him...

765
01:46:29,774 --> 01:46:32,504
- I didn't have any idea what...
- The fuck you didn't!

766
01:46:34,222 --> 01:46:36,349
The fuck you didn't.

767
01:46:36,845 --> 01:46:40,338
I did everything I could,
and I'm doing everything I can.

768
01:46:40,398 --> 01:46:42,730
Nice to see you.
I'm on my way to Florida.

769
01:46:42,830 --> 01:46:44,388
I'm doing everything I can.

770
01:46:44,525 --> 01:46:47,825
I'm sure. I didn't realize
you'd been out there to see him.

771
01:46:47,886 --> 01:46:51,151
Don't play games with me, Al.
Don't play stupid games.

772
01:46:51,214 --> 01:46:54,878
Nobody gets to go in there.
If I thought I could, I would.

773
01:46:55,566 --> 01:46:57,591
I've sent out hundreds of photographs.

774
01:46:57,709 --> 01:47:01,372
Every relief organization
on the Thai-Kampuchean border...

775
01:47:04,781 --> 01:47:08,581
...has got his picture. If I saw
one glimmer of hope, I'd go today.

776
01:47:08,941 --> 01:47:10,465
Life isn't a '40s movie.

777
01:47:10,605 --> 01:47:14,440
You can't just get on a plane and
make the whole world come out right!

778
01:47:15,821 --> 01:47:18,619
And I can't believe
I'm hearing this from you!

779
01:47:23,117 --> 01:47:24,414
Congrats.

780
01:47:26,348 --> 01:47:28,908
Do you keep in touch
with Dith Pran's family?

781
01:47:29,004 --> 01:47:31,200
Yes. They're living in San Francisco.

782
01:47:31,309 --> 01:47:34,176
How do you respond to accusations
that journalists...

783
01:47:34,252 --> 01:47:36,618
...underestimated the brutality
of the Khmer Rouge...

784
01:47:36,716 --> 01:47:40,448
...and so share responsibility for
what happened in Cambodia afterwards?

785
01:47:40,941 --> 01:47:42,772
We made a mistake.

786
01:47:43,244 --> 01:47:45,838
Maybe we underestimated
the kind of insanity...

787
01:47:45,932 --> 01:47:48,458
...that $ 7 billion worth
of bombing could produce.

788
01:47:48,556 --> 01:47:49,716
That is provocative...

789
01:47:49,868 --> 01:47:53,269
There have been a lot of refugee
stories in Reader's Digest...

790
01:47:53,324 --> 01:47:55,758
...about Cambodia.
Do you believe them?

791
01:47:55,851 --> 01:47:57,410
Don't you believe them?

792
01:47:57,548 --> 01:48:01,416
Maybe in this instance the
Reader's Digest happens to be correct.

793
01:48:01,452 --> 01:48:03,750
Do you apply the same disbelief
to stories...

794
01:48:03,851 --> 01:48:06,343
...that come out of Iran
or Palestine or Chile?

795
01:48:06,444 --> 01:48:08,810
Are refugees your next area
of interest?

796
01:48:08,907 --> 01:48:11,341
Will you be covering the boat people?

797
01:48:11,435 --> 01:48:12,561
No, I will not.

798
01:48:12,715 --> 01:48:14,411
Do you want a cup of tea?

799
01:48:15,276 --> 01:48:18,871
Are you looking around for some kind
of more salable suffering?

800
01:48:21,195 --> 01:48:23,824
I must have sent 500 letters.

801
01:48:29,002 --> 01:48:32,734
I wrote the International Red Cross,
the World Health Organization.

802
01:48:32,779 --> 01:48:35,475
I know you did, Syd.
You told me.

803
01:48:35,851 --> 01:48:38,115
I don't know who I didn't write to.

804
01:48:44,235 --> 01:48:46,897
I never really gave him any choice.

805
01:48:52,010 --> 01:48:55,138
One time we tried to discuss leaving.

806
01:49:03,594 --> 01:49:07,053
I talked to him about it,
but we never really discussed it.

807
01:49:10,090 --> 01:49:13,389
I discussed it with Swain and Rockoff.

808
01:49:17,097 --> 01:49:19,622
But I never discussed it with him.

809
01:49:30,249 --> 01:49:33,185
He stayed because
I wanted him to stay.

810
01:49:38,857 --> 01:49:40,722
And I stayed because...

811
01:53:11,076 --> 01:53:12,942
I'm trapped, Sydney.

812
01:53:13,060 --> 01:53:17,258
I know he suspects me,
and yet he treats me well.

813
01:53:17,699 --> 01:53:21,100
There are many different groups
over here, Sydney.

814
01:53:21,251 --> 01:53:23,345
I must take much care.

815
01:53:23,779 --> 01:53:27,840
Now Angka says we have new enemies.

816
01:53:28,195 --> 01:53:33,099
They say we must regain
our old lands from the Vietnamese.

817
01:53:33,635 --> 01:53:37,537
And now they say we must fight them.

818
01:53:39,107 --> 01:53:43,305
I miss you, my wife, my children.

819
01:53:43,330 --> 01:53:46,788
And my heart hungers for news of you.

820
01:54:09,794 --> 01:54:11,318
New China Radio reports...

821
01:54:11,457 --> 01:54:14,757
...that fighting between Vietnam
and Democratic Kampuchea...

822
01:54:14,818 --> 01:54:17,184
...has broken out
on a number of fronts.

823
01:54:17,346 --> 01:54:20,076
This is in retaliation,
according to the Vietnamese...

824
01:54:20,161 --> 01:54:22,595
...for a number of attacks
on border villages...

825
01:54:26,082 --> 01:54:27,447
Taxi driver, huh?

826
01:54:44,513 --> 01:54:46,344
I think you speak English.

827
01:54:46,720 --> 01:54:48,017
Sit down.

828
01:54:53,921 --> 01:54:56,446
You know, I love this country.

829
01:54:58,080 --> 01:55:00,879
I sacrificed everything for it.

830
01:55:02,177 --> 01:55:05,669
My wife died for the revolution.

831
01:55:07,361 --> 01:55:12,060
But the leaders of Angka
no longer trust the people.

832
01:55:12,768 --> 01:55:16,330
Therefore, I can no longer trust them.

833
01:55:17,952 --> 01:55:20,011
And they don't trust me.

834
01:55:22,336 --> 01:55:23,200
I fear...

835
01:55:24,512 --> 01:55:26,845
...really fear for the future.

836
01:55:30,976 --> 01:55:34,469
I think you love my son.

837
01:55:37,311 --> 01:55:38,573
For his sake...

838
01:55:39,551 --> 01:55:40,950
...look after him.

839
01:55:45,343 --> 01:55:47,937
The fighting is close by, Sydney.

840
01:55:48,031 --> 01:55:50,499
If the Vietnamese get here...

841
01:55:50,590 --> 01:55:52,752
...Angka will destroy everything...

842
01:55:54,719 --> 01:55:56,277
...and the Vietnamese,
they will find only ashes.

843
01:58:57,786 --> 01:59:01,222
I must try to stop the killing.
Good luck.

844
02:07:57,516 --> 02:07:59,416
Yeah, I'll be right there, Brian.

845
02:08:02,156 --> 02:08:06,115
Ann, get me 415-555-6421.

846
02:08:06,156 --> 02:08:07,851
Abe, I've got some great news!

847
02:08:20,460 --> 02:08:23,520
Twenty minutes ago, I get
a phone call from Paris.

848
02:08:23,595 --> 02:08:26,496
I get Andreas Freund.
He talked to Henry.

849
02:08:26,571 --> 02:08:28,665
He told him how to get in touch
with me.

850
02:08:28,779 --> 02:08:31,646
Freund says, "I have got
some great news for you."

851
02:08:31,723 --> 02:08:34,351
- San Francisco's on the line.
- "It's about Pran!"

852
02:08:34,603 --> 02:08:36,299
Is your mother there?

853
02:08:38,731 --> 02:08:39,891
When?

854
02:08:42,154 --> 02:08:44,817
All right,
I want you to get this down.

855
02:08:45,515 --> 02:08:48,177
No, write it down. Write it down.

856
02:08:49,546 --> 02:08:51,673
I've got a message from your dad!

857
02:10:01,544 --> 02:10:02,738
How you been?

858
02:10:15,240 --> 02:10:16,264
Do you forgive me?

859
02:10:16,904 --> 02:10:19,498
Nothing to forgive, Sydney.
Nothing.